The paper discusses interference alignment (IA) in multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the design of a training and feedback system, which is related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also considers the performance of IA in various fading scenarios, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of overhead-aware network design, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
